@{u}@{b}Working with disks@{uu}@{ub} is easy:
After you have mounted and formatted your drives they simply work like big floppies. Via SCSI software control you can @{b}Write-protect,  Read/Write protect, Unprotect, Unprotect till the next ejection@{ub} and  of course @{b}Eject@{ub} the disk.

The supplied ZIP Tools for the other platforms will do that for you. On the Amiga there is one @{" software packages " link toolsamiga} that can perform this tasks: the ZIP Tools from Oregon Research. (Also included by HISOFT with their ZIP-drive/Squirrel SCSI package for the A1200)

Christian Bauer (author of ShapeShifter) found out, what @{" SCSI commands " link zipcom} must be send to the ZIP. You can programm your own ZIP Tools.

@endnode

