@{u}@{b}Speed comparisons:@{uu}@{ub}

Determing the speed of a device is not so easy. A lot of people swear of DiskSpeed 4.2, but I thing DiskSpeed only tell you how it could be, not how it really is. Or do you know how large the buffers are your applications are using for disk-IO? And it stands in the contrary to the fact that more filesystem buffers (the buffers set in HDToolsbox) improve the speed of a device dramatically. I like more results that give you raw disk IO as found in SCSISpeed or SysInfo or comparisons for real file copy like Eckhard Ludwig did.

